author: Dan Duggan | NJ Advance Media for NJ.com
title: Rutgers vs. Indiana pregame notes: Looks like Hoosiers QB Nate Sudfeld will start
text:
Comments 
BLOOMINGTON, Ind. â€” We won't know for sure until the teams take the field shortly after 3:30 p.m., but all signs point to injured Indiana quarterback Nate Sudfeld starting today's game against Rutgers. 
Sudfeld's status has been questionable due to an ankle injury, but the senior quarterback fully participated in warmpus and took first-team reps. Sudfeld, who had both ankles taped, did not move with a noticeable limp in warmups. 
The status of Indiana's top running back, Jordan Howard, appears to be much more in doubt. Howard, who is also battling an ankle injury, dressed and participated in stretching, but sat out during drills and the team portion of warmups. 
Both players dressed for last week's 29-7 loss to Penn State, but neither played, so warmups don't provide a definitive answer. But Sudfeld's involvement certainly made it look like he'll be starting for the Hoosiers.
